Sentencas: In this study, we fabricated three dimensional yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) interface engineering layer (IEL) by using a DC sputtering method to enhance oxygen reduction reactions (ORRs) of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Three dimensional YSZ interface engineering layer for enhancement of oxygen reduction reactions of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In order to deposit three dimensional YSZ IEL, a commercial Y-Zr metal alloy target was sputtered under various deposition pressure conditions (4, 8, 12 Pa) and then annealed at 800 degrees C for 6 h. Phase transformation of metal alloy Y-Zr to YSZ was identified by X-ray diffraction, X-ray photoelectron spectroscopy and high resolution-transmission electron microscope.
Titulo: Three dimensional YSZ interface engineering layer for enhancement of oxygen reduction reactions of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The roughness of the three dimensional YSZ IELs were strongly related to the deposition pressure of the sputtering technique.
Titulo: Three dimensional YSZ interface engineering layer for enhancement of oxygen reduction reactions of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: After physical and chemical characterization, electrochemical examinations proved that the three dimensional YSZ IELs efficiently improved the ORR activity by geometrical effects.
Titulo: Three dimensional YSZ interface engineering layer for enhancement of oxygen reduction reactions of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The fuel cell with the IEL fabricated at 8 Pa condition achieved the best power density (37.9 mW/cm(2)), which was 30.2% improved performance compared to the fuel cell without IEL (29.1 mW/cm(2)).
Titulo: Three dimensional YSZ interface engineering layer for enhancement of oxygen reduction reactions of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy investigations also proved that rough three dimensional YSZ IELs efficiently enhance the performance of LT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Three dimensional YSZ interface engineering layer for enhancement of oxygen reduction reactions of low temperature solid oxide fuel cells
